    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "Money or other items used to facilitate transactions."
          example "Wampum was used as a currency by Amerindians."
        entry
          definition "(more specifically) Paper money."
        entry
          definition "The state of being current; general acceptance or recognition."
          example "The jargon’s currency."
        entry
          definition "Current value; general estimation; the rate at which anything is generally valued."
        entry
          definition "Fluency; readiness of utterance"
      partOfSpeech noun
